The Alex Jones Show
Tuesday, 16 July 2013


[sebaygo1]


Show Description
................

From the Infowars web site :: On this Tuesday, July 16 edition of The Alex Jones Show, Alex welcomes Staff Sergeant Joe Biggs to the broadcast. Biggs makes new revelations regarding the death of his late friend and former Rolling Stone contributing editor Michael Hastings. The journalist died June 18 when his Mercedes exploded so powerfully that first responders found its four-cylinder engine over 100 feet from the car. Los Angeles police and firefighters have since been ordered not to discuss the "accident." 

Marilu Henner, star of the hit TV sitcom Taxi and author of Total Health Makeover, joins the broadcast to discuss her ability to remember every minor detail in her life, a genetic trait called Highly Superior Auto-Biographical Memory. [The second half of hour two is largely an "infomercial" for Youngevity products that Jones and Henner promote.]

In Los Angeles, an anti-Zimmerman mob stormed a Wal-Mart, assaulting shoppers and starting fires. Overall, rioting has not been as widespread as some feared prior to the trial. 

Rock musician Ted Nugent is also on the show to expose how gun grabbers are taking advantage of Travyon Martin's death for a new assault on the Second Amendment.
